### Layer 5 — TikTok publishing (the hardest part)

This is where TikTok makes your life complicated.

**The API reality:**

TikTok's Content Posting API (`open.tiktokapis.com`) is the only official path. Key facts:
- Uses OAuth 2.0, MP4 up to 1 GB, max 25 videos/account/day
- Has two modes: Direct Post (public, requires audit) and Creator's Draft (goes to inbox, no audit needed)
- **The audit is the blocker**: your app must pass TikTok's manual review (2–4 weeks, multiple rounds) before Direct Post works publicly. Until then, every post is private
- Access tokens expire every 24 hours — you must implement token refresh in your automation
- Before every post, your app's UI must display the creator's username and avatar (TikTok verifies this during audit)

**Practical options:**

1. **Build + go through audit** — the right long-term path for a serious operation. Apply at developers.tiktok.com, document your use case clearly, implement the required UX compliance elements. Takes 2–6 weeks.

2. **Use a pre-audited API wrapper** — services like Zernio, Postiz, or Upload-Post have already passed the audit and expose a simple REST API you can call. Pricing is typically $10–20/1,000 posts. This is the fastest path to working automation.

3. **Creator's Draft mode** — available without audit. Posts go to your TikTok inbox as drafts; you or your team manually publish. Not fully automated, but functional while waiting for audit approval. Good for a hybrid workflow.

4. **Browser automation (Playwright/Puppeteer)** — technically possible, explicitly against TikTok's ToS, and fragile when TikTok changes its UI. Not recommended for anything you want to rely on.

**Recommended implementation:**

```javascript
// TikTok Content Posting API — Direct Post flow
async function postToTikTok(videoPath, caption, hashtags) {
  // Step 1: Get creator info
  const creatorInfo = await fetch('https://open.tiktokapis.com/v2/post/publish/creator_info/query/', {
    method: 'POST',
    headers: { 'Authorization': `Bearer ${accessToken}`, 'Content-Type': 'application/json' }
  });

  // Step 2: Initialize upload
  const init = await fetch('https://open.tiktokapis.com/v2/post/publish/video/init/', {
    method: 'POST',
    headers: { 'Authorization': `Bearer ${accessToken}`, 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },
    body: JSON.stringify({
      post_info: {
        title: caption,
        privacy_level: 'PUBLIC_TO_EVERYONE', // requires audit
        disable_duet: false,
        disable_stitch: false,
        video_cover_timestamp_ms: 1000
      },
      source_info: { source: 'FILE_UPLOAD', video_size: fileSize, chunk_size: chunkSize, total_chunk_count: chunks }
    })
  });
  const { publish_id, upload_url } = await init.json();

  // Step 3: Upload chunks
  // Step 4: Poll /v2/post/publish/status/fetch/ until PUBLISH_COMPLETE
}

// Token refresh (runs every 23 hours)
async function refreshToken(refreshToken) {
  const response = await fetch('https://open.tiktokapis.com/v2/oauth/token/', {
    method: 'POST',
    body: new URLSearchParams({ client_key, client_secret, grant_type: 'refresh_token', refresh_token: refreshToken })
  });
  return response.json(); // store new access_token and refresh_token
}
```

